>>LISA: My word was thank you.

00:29:06.230 --> 00:29:09.490 align:middle line:84%
I'm always in that place of
deep gratitude for whatever's

00:29:09.490 --> 00:29:13.920 align:middle line:84%
going on in my life, and it's
always been my first prayer.

00:29:13.920 --> 00:29:16.930 align:middle line:84%
And when you said my mind
was wandering, of course

00:29:16.930 --> 00:29:18.290 align:middle line:90%
it was wandering.

00:29:18.290 --> 00:29:21.820 align:middle line:84%
And I got back to-- and when
you said let go of the word

00:29:21.820 --> 00:29:26.550 align:middle line:84%
and let it just be, that is
such a great metaphor for life.

00:29:26.550 --> 00:29:31.260 align:middle line:84%
Whatever things are happening
in life, they are happening.

00:29:31.260 --> 00:29:34.520 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, letting them be
and not pushing and resisting

00:29:34.520 --> 00:29:37.320 align:middle line:84%
against them-- just
that practice of letting

00:29:37.320 --> 00:29:41.090 align:middle line:84%
it drop and float was a
beautiful metaphor for me

00:29:41.090 --> 00:29:41.800 align:middle line:90%
in life.

00:29:41.800 --> 00:29:43.530 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: That's
a wonderful insight.

00:29:43.530 --> 00:29:44.654 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That was wonderful.

00:29:44.654 --> 00:29:47.140 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: Yeah, because
contemplative prayer

00:29:47.140 --> 00:29:49.292 align:middle line:90%
is like learning to float.

