00:31:45.200 --> 00:31:48.430 align:middle line:84%
health, healing, whatever's
going on in my life

00:31:48.430 --> 00:31:49.120 align:middle line:90%
at that moment.

00:31:49.120 --> 00:31:51.300 align:middle line:90%
I extend that to my family.

00:31:51.300 --> 00:31:54.820 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, I forget to
extend it beyond to the world

00:31:54.820 --> 00:31:58.370 align:middle line:84%
because I don't feel-- there's
a certain-- I want more

00:31:58.370 --> 00:32:02.070 align:middle line:84%
of a focus, and it
seems so broad to me.

00:32:02.070 --> 00:32:07.530 align:middle line:84%
How do I take that broadness
of world peace and pray

00:32:07.530 --> 00:32:10.200 align:middle line:84%
for something that
seems so ambiguous?

00:32:10.200 --> 00:32:12.580 align:middle line:84%
I guess my mental
monkey mind wants

00:32:12.580 --> 00:32:15.130 align:middle line:90%
to grab on to the solution.

00:32:15.130 --> 00:32:16.230 align:middle line:90%
It does, yeah.

00:32:16.230 --> 00:32:18.810 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: Well, one thing
that might be helpful, or see

00:32:18.810 --> 00:32:25.910 align:middle line:84%
what this is like-- have the
attitude of that silent-- that

00:32:25.910 --> 00:32:30.980 align:middle line:84%
period of gratitude, like
the centering prayer.

00:32:30.980 --> 00:32:33.490 align:middle line:84%
We're really uniting
ourselves with everybody

00:32:33.490 --> 00:32:36.540 align:middle line:90%
at the depths of existence.

00:32:36.540 --> 00:32:41.510 align:middle line:84%
So it's kind of a prayer for
everyone when we do that.

00:32:41.510 --> 00:32:43.490 align:middle line:84%
And yet, at the same
time, sometimes it's

00:32:43.490 --> 00:32:48.100 align:middle line:84%
valuable at the end to
remember particular needs.

00:32:48.100 --> 00:32:51.560 align:middle line:84%
But if your heart opens
to your family, you know,

00:32:51.560 --> 00:32:52.760 align:middle line:90%
that's what's relevant.

00:32:52.760 --> 00:32:54.103 align:middle line:90%
That's what's here.

00:32:54.103 --> 00:32:54.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:32:54.790 --> 00:32:56.262 align:middle line:90%
So not judging myself about it.

00:32:56.262 --> 00:32:57.970 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: Yeah, I
think it's beautiful.

00:32:57.970 --> 00:32:59.595 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I think this
could go on and on

00:32:59.595 --> 00:33:03.060 align:middle line:84%
about letting go of judgment,
letting go of self-judgment.

00:33:03.060 --> 00:33:05.310 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure you--
so when you're

00:33:05.310 --> 00:33:07.770 align:middle line:84%
teaching this, what are
the questions that come up

00:33:07.770 --> 00:33:08.320 align:middle line:90%
from people?

00:33:08.320 --> 00:33:12.660 align:middle line:84%
What are the biggest questions
that arise in your classes?

00:33:12.660 --> 00:33:14.160 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: It
depends on the class.

00:33:14.160 --> 00:33:15.720 align:middle line:84%
If it's an introductory
class, it's

00:33:15.720 --> 00:33:17.600 align:middle line:84%
usually about how
to do the practice.

00:33:17.600 --> 00:33:19.810 align:middle line:84%
Actually, you asked a
question a few minutes ago,

00:33:19.810 --> 00:33:25.080 align:middle line:84%
which is more representative
of an advanced question.

00:33:25.080 --> 00:33:26.970 align:middle line:84%
I think you asked
something about how would I

00:33:26.970 --> 00:33:31.100 align:middle line:84%
counsel someone with trauma
or psychological issues.

00:33:31.100 --> 00:33:31.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:33:31.800 --> 00:33:34.110 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: So taking
that up a little bit,

00:33:34.110 --> 00:33:37.150 align:middle line:90%
catching that question again.

00:33:37.150 --> 00:33:40.375 align:middle line:84%
The centering prayer and some
of those auxiliary practices

00:33:40.375 --> 00:33:45.310 align:middle line:84%
that I mentioned are great
helps for being in the world.

00:33:45.310 --> 00:33:47.990 align:middle line:84%
But as a trained
psychotherapist,

00:33:47.990 --> 00:33:50.130 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't recommend
them as being

00:33:50.130 --> 00:33:55.150 align:middle line:84%
exclusive of other forms
of assistance-- body work,

00:33:55.150 --> 00:33:58.330 align:middle line:84%
therapy, good
support, being rooted

00:33:58.330 --> 00:34:02.350 align:middle line:84%
with good medical-- alternative
medicine and regular medicine.

00:34:02.350 --> 00:34:05.060 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, people come
into a meditation class

00:34:05.060 --> 00:34:07.502 align:middle line:84%
or they get into a
practice of meditation,

00:34:07.502 --> 00:34:08.960 align:middle line:84%
and they think,
well, this is going

00:34:08.960 --> 00:34:12.250 align:middle line:90%
to be my answer for everything.

00:34:12.250 --> 00:34:17.390 align:middle line:84%
And I think actually, honestly,
it's the most profound answer,

00:34:17.390 --> 00:34:20.510 align:middle line:84%
to touch into what
we're talking about.

00:34:20.510 --> 00:34:22.270 align:middle line:84%
But to live that
out in the world,

00:34:22.270 --> 00:34:26.370 align:middle line:84%
I recommend taking advantage
of the supports that

00:34:26.370 --> 00:34:28.030 align:middle line:90%
have been developed.

00:34:28.030 --> 00:34:31.210 align:middle line:84%
There's something called
spiritual bypassing,

00:34:31.210 --> 00:34:34.900 align:middle line:84%
this attitude that if I'm a
real spiritual practitioner,

00:34:34.900 --> 00:34:38.960 align:middle line:84%
I can bypass everything else,
rather than take advantage,

00:34:38.960 --> 00:34:40.810 align:middle line:84%
and listen, and
learn from what I

00:34:40.810 --> 00:34:44.330 align:middle line:84%
need to have in my life,
especially support.

00:34:44.330 --> 00:34:46.690 align:middle line:90%
Our society is kind of isolated.

00:34:46.690 --> 00:34:48.880 align:middle line:90%
We lose connection with people.

00:34:48.880 --> 00:34:51.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, and
in a sense, develop

00:34:51.270 --> 00:34:54.050 align:middle line:84%
some type of a spiritual
ignorance of what else

00:34:54.050 --> 00:34:57.705 align:middle line:84%
is around, what is going on,
and-- a disconnection that way.

00:34:57.705 --> 00:35:00.830 align:middle line:84%
And I'm all about
bridging that gap.

00:35:00.830 --> 00:35:03.870 align:middle line:84%
That's, I think, one of
the main-- my main passions

00:35:03.870 --> 00:35:08.580 align:middle line:84%
is bridging the gap of
deeply profound practices

00:35:08.580 --> 00:35:13.720 align:middle line:84%
to the practical daily
life of ordinary people

00:35:13.720 --> 00:35:17.930 align:middle line:84%
who go through stressors in
life, and it hooks you in.

00:35:17.930 --> 00:35:18.846 align:middle line:90%
>>FRENETTE: That's it.

00:35:18.846 --> 00:35:20.647 align:middle line:90%
That's part of our reality.

00:35:20.647 --> 00:35:21.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It is.

00:35:21.230 --> 00:35:21.890 align:middle line:90%
>>FRENETTE: Respond to it.

00:35:21.890 --> 00:35:22.681 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:35:22.681 --> 00:35:23.730 align:middle line:90%
It's part of our reality.

00:35:23.730 --> 00:35:25.855 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: And that's--
your point about religion.

00:35:25.855 --> 00:35:29.550 align:middle line:84%
I think religion, then, needs
to respond to people's life

00:35:29.550 --> 00:35:30.740 align:middle line:90%
in this world.

00:35:30.740 --> 00:35:32.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's a bit
disconnected because it's

00:35:32.740 --> 00:35:34.330 align:middle line:90%
held on to the tradition.

00:35:34.330 --> 00:35:38.830 align:middle line:84%
And I understand the tradition,
and it's deep, and it's rooted.

00:35:38.830 --> 00:35:41.140 align:middle line:84%
But there's got to be a way
for the tradition to exist

00:35:41.140 --> 00:35:44.830 align:middle line:84%
and at the same time to make
it practical to modern life.

00:35:44.830 --> 00:35:46.370 align:middle line:90%
And this is a nice balance.

00:35:46.370 --> 00:35:49.870 align:middle line:84%
This is a nice kind of
stepping stone on that path.

00:35:49.870 --> 00:35:52.921 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: Yeah, I think
it's one helpful contribution

00:35:52.921 --> 00:35:53.420 align:middle line:90%
to that.

00:35:53.420 --> 00:35:56.315 align:middle line:84%
But I think that's the
challenge for religion

00:35:56.315 --> 00:35:59.380 align:middle line:84%
and religious institutions,
and all of society.

00:35:59.380 --> 00:36:02.120 align:middle line:84%
We're in this evolving
world, and what's

00:36:02.120 --> 00:36:05.660 align:middle line:84%
the relevance from the past
that needs to be updated?

00:36:05.660 --> 00:36:07.110 align:middle line:84%
That was the
original inspiration

00:36:07.110 --> 00:36:12.280 align:middle line:84%
for centering prayer, to bring
forth this contemplative wisdom

00:36:12.280 --> 00:36:14.880 align:middle line:84%
out of the monasteries
so it could

00:36:14.880 --> 00:36:16.290 align:middle line:90%
be relevant to people's lives.

00:36:16.290 --> 00:36:17.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I
love the mission.

00:36:17.680 --> 00:36:19.890 align:middle line:84%
And I think-- this is
just my personal opinion,

00:36:19.890 --> 00:36:21.550 align:middle line:90%
but going back to the trauma.

00:36:21.550 --> 00:36:26.250 align:middle line:84%
In this day and age,
when things move so fast,

00:36:26.250 --> 00:36:28.750 align:middle line:84%
little events happen
in our daily lives

00:36:28.750 --> 00:36:32.100 align:middle line:84%
that are traumatic, that
do get stored in the body.

00:36:32.100 --> 00:36:35.300 align:middle line:84%
They don't have to be major
life-changing traumas.

00:36:35.300 --> 00:36:41.220 align:middle line:84%
It could be a bad
rapport with somebody,

00:36:41.220 --> 00:36:43.630 align:middle line:84%
exchanged words
that are hurtful.

00:36:43.630 --> 00:36:47.120 align:middle line:84%
It could be-- those little
things register in our bodies

00:36:47.120 --> 00:36:48.950 align:middle line:90%
as traumas during the day.

00:36:48.950 --> 00:36:51.610 align:middle line:84%
We stack them up at
night, go to sleep,

00:36:51.610 --> 00:36:53.360 align:middle line:90%
and start all over the next day.

00:36:53.360 --> 00:36:56.470 align:middle line:84%
There's got to be a way
to be able to release

00:36:56.470 --> 00:37:00.560 align:middle line:84%
those mini-- mini crises
throughout your day,

00:37:00.560 --> 00:37:02.980 align:middle line:84%
and this is a good
way to do that.

00:37:02.980 --> 00:37:06.960 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: It's a good way
to help with that process.

00:37:06.960 --> 00:37:10.390 align:middle line:84%
My abba, Thomas Keating,
he has this image

00:37:10.390 --> 00:37:14.410 align:middle line:84%
that the divine, God,
in this relationship

00:37:14.410 --> 00:37:16.650 align:middle line:90%
is a divine psychotherapist--

00:37:16.650 --> 00:37:17.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, that's great.

00:37:17.750 --> 00:37:21.000 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: --who is
helping to heal that.

00:37:21.000 --> 00:37:24.330 align:middle line:84%
But again, I think that some
of the traumas and the pace--

00:37:24.330 --> 00:37:26.700 align:middle line:84%
just as you're saying,
the pace of life--

00:37:26.700 --> 00:37:28.836 align:middle line:90%
is inherently traumatic for us.

00:37:28.836 --> 00:37:30.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It definitely
has those-- yeah,

00:37:30.460 --> 00:37:31.464 align:middle line:90%
those days happen.

00:37:31.464 --> 00:37:33.630 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: That we need a
lot of other things, too.

00:37:33.630 --> 00:37:34.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I think I want
to go back to your point

00:37:34.740 --> 00:37:36.390 align:middle line:84%
at the beginning
about listening,

00:37:36.390 --> 00:37:38.050 align:middle line:84%
about that inner
psychotherapist.

00:37:38.050 --> 00:37:42.480 align:middle line:84%
I love that concept of asking
the divine, or whatever

00:37:42.480 --> 00:37:45.930 align:middle line:84%
it is that your presence
is, what can I do?

00:37:45.930 --> 00:37:47.460 align:middle line:90%
What is the solution?

00:37:47.460 --> 00:37:49.040 align:middle line:90%
How can I heal?

00:37:49.040 --> 00:37:49.950 align:middle line:90%
What is this?

00:37:49.950 --> 00:37:52.640 align:middle line:84%
What is the-- that is not
in my current awareness?

00:37:52.640 --> 00:37:54.454 align:middle line:84%
What can-- and then,
just to listen.

00:37:54.454 --> 00:37:55.620 align:middle line:90%
>>FRENETTE: To listen, yeah.

00:37:55.620 --> 00:37:58.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it's
usually always there.

00:37:58.010 --> 00:37:59.901 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if it
comes from our own minds

00:37:59.901 --> 00:38:01.650 align:middle line:84%
or if it really does
come from the divine.

00:38:01.650 --> 00:38:03.366 align:middle line:90%
What do you think?

00:38:03.366 --> 00:38:05.240 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: I think it
comes from the divine,

00:38:05.240 --> 00:38:07.560 align:middle line:84%
but of course, it's filtered
through our own minds.

00:38:07.560 --> 00:38:11.220 align:middle line:84%
So I like this image that
you're kind of describing--

00:38:11.220 --> 00:38:15.420 align:middle line:84%
to ask, and then to listen,
and to ask again, and listen.

00:38:15.420 --> 00:38:17.980 align:middle line:84%
It's like-- it is a
living relationship.

00:38:17.980 --> 00:38:21.604 align:middle line:84%
And then, we get more in touch
with the divine, I think.

00:38:21.604 --> 00:38:23.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Are there any
other profound teachings

00:38:23.520 --> 00:38:26.560 align:middle line:84%
that you want to share with us
from your journey with Thomas

00:38:26.560 --> 00:38:30.689 align:middle line:84%
Keating or your entire
journey with the movement?

00:38:30.689 --> 00:38:32.230 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: I think
I would just like

00:38:32.230 --> 00:38:36.280 align:middle line:84%
to emphasize for myself
and for the people

00:38:36.280 --> 00:38:39.995 align:middle line:84%
that I know and
work with that it

00:38:39.995 --> 00:38:44.220 align:middle line:84%
is a journey into being
more and more human.

00:38:44.220 --> 00:38:47.730 align:middle line:84%
This is this traditional
teaching in Christianity

00:38:47.730 --> 00:38:49.670 align:middle line:84%
that, through this
contemplative process,

00:38:49.670 --> 00:38:55.240 align:middle line:84%
one is divinized, meaning that
the life of God awakens and one

00:38:55.240 --> 00:38:57.320 align:middle line:90%
becomes divinized.

00:38:57.320 --> 00:39:00.942 align:middle line:84%
But I also think, for me, it's
becoming more and more human.

00:39:00.942 --> 00:39:02.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a great point.

00:39:02.150 --> 00:39:05.190 align:middle line:84%
>>FRENETTE: Yeah,
so-- just who I am.

00:39:05.190 --> 00:39:06.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great point.

00:39:06.540 --> 00:39:09.690 align:middle line:84%
Well, thank you so much for
enlightening me and sharing

00:39:09.690 --> 00:39:13.376 align:middle line:90%
with me with your whole process.

00:39:13.376 --> 00:39:15.250 align:middle line:84%
I didn't look at my
notes at all because they

00:39:15.250 --> 00:39:17.200 align:middle line:84%
had nothing to do with
what we just talked about.

00:39:17.200 --> 00:39:18.158 align:middle line:90%
>>FRENETTE: Yeah, Lisa.

